   9 import click

  11 from click import MultiCommand

  13 find_unsafe = re.compile(r'[^\w@%+=:,./-]').search
  14 
  15 
  16 def single_quote(s):
  17     """Escape a string with single quotes in order to be parsed as a single element by shlex
  18 
  19     Parameters
  20     ----------
  21     s : str
  22         The string to quote
  23 
  24     Returns
  25     -------
  26     str
  27        The quoted string
  28     """
  29     if not s:
  30         return "''"
  31     if find_unsafe(s) is None:
  32         return s
  33 
  34     # use single quotes, and put single quotes into double quotes
  35     # the string $'b is then quoted as '$'"'"'b'
  36     return "'" + s.replace("'", "'\"'\"'") + "'"
  37 
  38 
  39 def double_quote(s):
  40     """Escape a string with double quotes in order to be parsed as a single element by shlex
  41 
  42     Parameters
  43     ----------
  44     s : str
  45         The string to quote
  46 
  47     Returns
  48     -------
  49     str
  50        The quoted string
  51     """
  52     if not s:
  53         return '""'
  54     if find_unsafe(s) is None:
  55         return s
  56 
  57     # use double quotes, and put double quotes into single quotes
  58     # the string $"b is then quoted as "$"'"'"b"
  59     return '"' + s.replace('"', '"\'"\'"') + '"'

  62 def resolve_ctx(cli, prog_name, args, resilient_parsing=True):
  63     """
  64 
  65     Parameters
  66     ----------
  67     cli : click.Command
  68         The main click Command of the program
  69     prog_name : str
  70         The program name on the command line
  71     args : [str]
  72         The arguments already written by the user on the command line
  73 
  74     Returns
  75     -------
  76     click.core.Context
  77         A new context corresponding to the current command
  78     """
  79     ctx = cli.make_context(prog_name, list(args), resilient_parsing=resilient_parsing)
  80     while ctx.args + ctx.protected_args and isinstance(ctx.command, MultiCommand):
  81         a = ctx.protected_args + ctx.args
  82         cmd = ctx.command.get_command(ctx, a[0])
  83         if cmd is None:
  84             return None
  85         if hasattr(cmd, "no_args_is_help"):
  86             no_args_is_help = cmd.no_args_is_help
  87             cmd.no_args_is_help = False
  88         ctx = cmd.make_context(a[0], a[1:], parent=ctx, resilient_parsing=resilient_parsing)
  89         if hasattr(cmd, "no_args_is_help"):
  90             cmd.no_args_is_help = no_args_is_help
  91     return ctx

  94 def split_args(line):
  95     """Version of shlex.split that silently accept incomplete strings.
  96 
  97     Parameters
  98     ----------
  99     line : str
 100         The string to split
 101 
 102     Returns
 103     -------
 104     [str]
 105         The line split in separated arguments
 106     """
 107     lex = shlex.shlex(line, posix=True)
 108     lex.whitespace_split = True
 109     lex.commenters = ''
 110     res = []
 111     try:
 112         while True:
 113             res.append(next(lex))
 114     except ValueError:  # No closing quotation
 115         pass
 116     except StopIteration:  # End of loop
 117         pass
 118     if lex.token:
 119         res.append(lex.token)
 120     return res

 122 
 123 def get_auto_shell():
 124     """Returns the current shell"""
 125     return shellingham.detect_shell()[0]
